# {{lb|fr|legal}} [[on or about]] (a date).
#: {{ux|fr|Jean Tremblay, à Montréal, '''le ou vers le''' 9 juillet 2020, a commis un vol.|Jean Tremblay, at Montreal, '''on or about''' July 9, 2020, committed theft.}}

====Usage notes====
* Used with respect to a date, in order to provide the date but to avoid invalidating the statement if the date should be inaccurate. It replaces the {{m|fr|le}} that normally introduces dates.
